28/04/2004
COLOGNE, Germany -- Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder met with Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Tuesday (27 April) and expressed Germany's support for Turkey's EU membership bid. 
Schroeder said that if the country meets accession criteria, it should be accepted in the Union. 
He also stressed the importance of Turkey's membership in the EU in terms of security. 
Erdogan, in turn, suggested that the Turkish and German economies could develop into an "engine" for EU economic growth. 
(Hurriyet - 28/04/04; Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 27/04/04)
